The paper deals with extracting semantic relations from non-figurative texts, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. The focus is on obtaining prior knowledge on the usual modality and affordance estimates of entities, which are important concepts in artificial intelligence (AI) and computer vision (CV). The paper also discusses possible feature and learning framework adoption, which are relevant topics in machine learning (ML) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.LG, followed by cs.CV and cs.IR.
